  "text": "Because Bacteroides have been previously shown to be strong drivers of T reg induction [CITATION_1] , we reasoned that the BOM T regs would mediate theta OMVs (75 g/ml: n = 7, six experiments; 37.5 g/ml: n = 6, six experiments; 18.75 g/ml: n = 5, four experiments; 10 g/ml: n = 8, six experiments; 1 g/ml: n = 3, three experiments; 0.1 g/ml: n = 4, four experiments; 0.01 g/ml: n = 3, three experiments). Flow cytometry plots are gated on CD4 + CD45.1 + leukocytes.",
